# 7. ヒーロー、参上！

Tsukasa: You have to stop it...?
Inuyama: Yes, we've decided to stop and inspect it since it seems to be acting up a bit.
Inuyama: But figuring out the cause may take some time.
Tsukasa: I see...
Guests: Hey, it looks like the Ferris wheel is down for repairs...
Guests: Wait, really? Aww, I was really looking forward to going on it...
Mizuki: Oh no...
Inuyama: Our hands are tied since we must put safety first...
Inuyama: That being said... I feel absolutely terrible about disappointing the guests like this during the last day...
Tsukasa: Mr. Inuyama...
Inuyama: But I'm satisfied. I started this carnival with the dream of putting smiles on the faces of people all over.
Inuyama: And I've successfully accomplished that.
Tsukasa: (This place means everything to Mr. Inuyama... It's designed to make all those who attend smile and laugh.)
Tsukasa: (And now both he and his guests are going to spend their final day here frowning...)
Tsukasa: (Isn't there anything we can do...?)
Tsukasa: (Isn't there a way we can make it so everybody here goes home smiling?)
Tsukasa: This is all I can conjure up.
Nene: Huh?
Tsukasa: Mr. Inuyama, all of you... Would you mind listening for a minute?
Tsukasa: I have an idea.
Children: Hey, we wanna go on the Ferris wheel! When's it gonna be fixed?!
Guests: Hmm... I'm not sure... This may take quite a while.
Guests: It's too bad, but we'll just have to go on something else. What about that merry-go-round? Doesn't riding cats sound like fun?
Children: We wanna go on the Ferris wheel!
???: “Over here, Sis!”
Children: Huh?
Older Cat Sister: “Hehe. So this is the carnival's main attraction. The Ferris wheel. It's the perfect target for a big prank.”
Younger Cat Sister: “Yeah, it is. Let's see... Where are the controls...? Let's try checking over there!”
Children: Hey, they went away...!
Guests: What were they doing just now...?
Guests: Those girls had really cute cat ears on...
???: “Oh, pardon me!”
Nyantaro: “I have a question for all of you... Did any of you see a pair of cat sisters pass by here just now?”
Guests: Wait, is he talking about those girls we just saw...?
Children: Whoa, this cat's wearing a cape...! That's so cool...!
Guests: Is something about to happen...?
Nyantaro: “The thing is, a pair of mischievous cats have been causing trouble at this carnival recently. I was chasing after them because they're likely up to no good again...”
Nyantaro: “But I seem to have lost them. So, any information that you can provide would be greatly appreciated!”
Children: Umm... They went that way! They even talked about pulling a prank or something!
Nyantaro: “What?! That's terrible...! Thank you, young man!”
Guests: Oh, is this some sort of event...?
Guests: Maybe. I mean, the person we just talked to was totally wearing a superhero costume!
Guest: “No, look! The Ferris wheel's stuck!”
Guest: “Oh no! But it was moving a second ago. What do you think happened...?”
Guest: “Hey, do you guys know what happened?”
Children: We don't know!
Guest: “Hmm... But the door to the control room is open... Wait, huh?”
Guest: “The switch is gone! No, did those cat sisters steal it...?”
Children: What...?! The Ferris wheel stopped because of those cat sisters, Mommy...!
Guests: Wow... So, does that mean it stopping is also a part of this show...?
Miku: (Wow, Tsukasa, that's amazing...! You turned what happened to the Ferris wheel into part of the show☆)
Miku: (Plus...)
Children: Hmm... Where do you think those cat sisters went?
???: “Oh, you rang?”
Children: Huh...?
Older Cat Sister: “Heh heh heh...”
Older Cat Sister: “Are you looking for this switch?”
Older Cat Sister: “Well, it's ours now...!”
Older Cat Sister: “If you want it back, you'll have to catch us first!”
Younger Cat Sister: “But there's no way that's gonna happen.”
Children: Hey, cat man! They're over there!
Nyantaro: “Hm?! I'll be darned! Thank you, everyone!”
Nyantaro: “Stopping the Ferris wheel... How could you do such a thing? I am not letting you two get away this time!”
Nyantaro: “I, Nyantaro the cat hero, will put an end to your antics! So, freeze!”
Children: Wow, he's a cat hero...! You can do it, Nyantaro!
Children: But the cat sisters are also really cute...! Run for it, you two!
Miku: (They've managed to turn the guests' frowns upside down!)
Nyantaro: “Ah, I have you now! Give me the switch...”
Younger Cat Sister: “Sis, take it!”
Nyantaro: “What...?!”
Nyantaro: “Grr...! Credit where credit's due, they're working in perfect sync. I've lost them again...”
Nyantaro: “Do any of you happen to know where those despicable cat sisters went?”
Children: Nyantaro, over there!
Nyantaro: “Huh?”
Guests: Oh, the little sister's back that way!
Nyantaro: “That way...? Ah, underneath the Ferris wheel! Thank you! I'll take a look now!”
Older Cat Sister: “Seriously, why are you being such a pest today?!”
Nyantaro: “Of course I'm being a pest. For the sake of the guests waiting to ride the Ferris wheel, I can't afford to give up...!”
Children: Nyantaro...!
Guest: “Hey, everyone, why don't we all show Nyantaro our support?”
Guest: “Our cheers might give him the boost of energy he needs to succeed!”
Guest: “Yeah, you're right! Let's all cheer for him, you guys!”
Guest: “Yes, I'm talking to you!”
Children: Oh... O-Okay!
Guest: “Ready?! One, two, three...!”
Guest: “You can do it, Nyantaro!”
Children: You can do it!
Nyantaro: “Huff... Huff... They're so fast! Despite you all cheering me on, I can't seem to catch them...!”
Guests: Is Nyantaro gonna be okay...?
Tsukasa: (They should be finished fixing the Ferris wheel soon...)
Tsukasa: (No, it looks like they still need more time. In that case, we can try moving over towards that group of guests and—)
Miku: <Tsukasa, Tsukasa...!>
Tsukasa: Huh?! Miku?!
Miku: <Look over there...! The sign!>
Tsukasa: Th-The sign...?
Tsukasa: (Mr. Inuyama's taking down the “Under Repair” sign! That must mean...)
Tsukasa: (The Ferris wheel is ready to run again...!)
Miku: <Looks like he's signaling the okay☆>
Tsukasa: Yes, which means...!
Nyantaro: “Alright, playtime is over! I'm going to catch you two once and for all!”
Nyantaro: “Here we goooooo...!!”
Younger Cat Sister: “H-He looks really determined...! Sis, take the switch and...”
Younger Cat Sister: “N-No...! It slipped...”
Nyantaro: “Yes, got it!”
Children: Yes...! Nyantaro got it back!
Nyantaro: “Now I just need to flip the switch...”
Nyantaro: “And start it back up!”
Guests: Huh...?
Guests: Th-The Ferris wheel's working again...! Does this mean we can go on it now...?!
Children: That was so cool! Thanks, Nyantaro!
Nyantaro: “Hah hah hah! There's no need to thank me!”
Nyantaro: “After all, it's a hero's job to make sure everybody keeps smiling!”
Nyantaro: “The memories you make here today... I hope they make you smile for years to come.”
Nyantaro: “And let me say... Thank you all for visiting today!”
